name: openapi-schema-pydantic
summary: openapi (v3) specification schema as pydantic class
documentation_summary: The HTML text is about the "openapi-schema-pydantic" package available on PyPI (Python Package Index). It is a library that allows the OpenAPI (v3) specification schema to be represented as Pydantic classes, facilitating the construction of OpenAPI documents using Python objects, dictionaries, or a mix of both. The package, version 1.2.4, was released on June 29, 2022, and requires Python version 3.6.1 or newer. It is licensed under the MIT License and is OS independent. The document also includes examples of how to use the library to create OpenAPI documents and how to use Pydantic classes as schema objects for more complex data structures. Additionally, it mentions browser compatibility warnings for IE9 and below, and the importance of enabling JavaScript for full functionality.
